    diagnostics: ["A1C level: diagnostic threshold ≥6.5% for diabetes (ADA/CDA); 5.7-6.4% prediabetes (ADA), 6.0-6.4% (CDA); correlate with fasting glucose and OGTT","Fasting plasma glucose (FPG): ≥126 mg/dL (7.0 mmol/L) confirms diabetes; 100-125 mg/dL impaired fasting glucose","Oral glucose tolerance test (OGTT): 2-hour value ≥200 mg/dL diagnostic for diabetes; gold standard for gestational diabetes screening","Continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) data: time in range 70-180 mg/dL complements A1C; captures glycemic variability A1C cannot detect","Fructosamine: reflects average glucose over 2-3 weeks; useful when A1C is unreliable (hemoglobinopathies, hemolytic anemia, recent transfusion)","Assess for conditions causing falsely elevated A1C: iron deficiency anemia, splenectomy, chronic kidney disease, alcoholism","Assess for conditions causing falsely low A1C: hemolytic anemia, acute blood loss, pregnancy, hemoglobin variants (HbS, HbC, HbF)"],
